<item>
            <title>[SOLR-244] ModifiableSolrParams -- (perhaps) modify MultiMapSolrParams</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-244</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The existing ways to change parameters at runtime are awkward, this is a class I have been using in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-20&quot; title=&quot;A simple Java client for updating and searching&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-20&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-20&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  It is a solr params implementation with two nice additions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  public void set( String name, String ... val ) &lt;/p&gt;
{
   ... 
  }

&lt;p&gt;  public void add( String name, String ... val ) &lt;/p&gt;
{
  ...
  }

&lt;p&gt;Rather then have a new class, it may be better to augment MultiMapSolrParams to include a default constructor and use set/add to modify the final Map&amp;lt;String,String[]&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
