                            <comment id="12497702" author="ryantxu" created="Tue, 22 May 2007 06:23:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This includes a new class (with tests) and augments MultiMapSolrParams with set() and add()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only one of the changes should be included &amp;#8211; unless there is a good reason &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; to augment MultiMapSolrParams, I think that is a better solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I know all of this is possible with the existing interface, but I prefer:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    MultiMapSolrParams params = new MultiMapSolrParams();&lt;br/&gt;
    params.add( &quot;name&quot;, &quot;value1&quot; );&lt;br/&gt;
    ...&lt;br/&gt;
    params.set( &quot;name&quot;, &quot;value2&quot;, &quot;value3&quot; );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Map&amp;lt;String,String[]&amp;gt; map = new HashMap&amp;lt;String, String[]&amp;gt;(); &lt;br/&gt;
    MultiMapSolrParams params = new MultiMapSolrParams( map );&lt;br/&gt;
    MultiMapSolrParams.addParam( &quot;name&quot;, &quot;value1&quot;, map );&lt;br/&gt;
    ...&lt;br/&gt;
    map.put( &quot;name&quot;, new String[] &lt;/p&gt;
{ &quot;value2&quot;, &quot;value3&quot; }
&lt;p&gt; );&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
